column2: The Sacrificers believe that any rewards that might be obtained from the worship of various sanctioned deities and spirits pale in comparison to the rewards offered to those that are willing to make the appropriate sacrifices to powers that are less restrained by such petty concerns as "morality", "decency", and "laws". Though there are many conflicting stories as to what the Sacrificers are doing and some of these are quite fanciful, all agree that human sacrifice is a common element of their dark ceremonies.
Attempt to find out whether §Y[Root.GetTitledFirstName]§! is open to the power of the occult. If so, you may invite [Root.GetHerHim] to become a member of the Sacrificers.
Has not been approached by the Sacrificers before.

The Underworld Triad distinguish themselves from various subversive groups seeking to overthrow those that claim to possess the Mandate of Heaven by instead denying it entirely. Instead, members of the brotherhood seek to amass supernatural power for reasons ranging from petty to grand, and see nothing wrong with offering horrifying sacrifices to less benign gods and spirits if it will further their own goals.
Attempt to find out whether §Y[Root.GetTitledFirstName]§! is open to the power of the occult. If so, you may invite [Root.GetHerHim] to become a member of the Underworld Triad.
Has not been approached by the Ghost Gatherers before.
The leader of the Underworld Triad.

Craving power over all else, the members of the Ghost Gatherers are willing to make terrible sacrifices to dark spirits in order to further their own goals. As long as someone else is paying the price, the brotherhood sees nothing wrong with making someone die a horrible death, and as far as they are concerned the vengeful ghosts of the deceased causing the living any trouble is just an added bonus.
Attempt to find out whether §Y[Root.GetTitledFirstName]§! is open to the power of the occult. If so, you may invite [Root.GetHerHim] to become a member of the Ghost Gatherers.
Has not been approached by the Ghost Gatherers before.
The leader of the Ghost Gatherers.

The secretive brotherhood known as the Procession of Pox goes far beyond making the proper shamanic rituals to accomodate Daebyeolsangsin, the god of pox, seeking to gain dark powers from him. Though only the maddest among them would seek to spread disease, all of the brotherhood's members are willing to cause suffering if it furthers their personal goals.
Recruit to the Procession of Pox
